id: pm-z0ip
title: 2026-06-01 package ecosystem SDK agent UX audit and hardening
description: "Detailed manual audit, temp-project dogfood, SDK/ecosystem review, agent-optimized UX review, telemetry/Sentry validation, CI/PR review loop, and targeted hardening on latest main. Duplicate check: pm search found prior closed broad-audit lineage pm-59gj/pm-kd9n/pm-etxf/pm-qmx3 and no in-progress audit items; this task records the new June 1 requested pass."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[7]: agent-ux,audit,ci,ecosystem,package-first,sdk,telemetry
created_at: "2026-06-01T20:57:09.204Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-01T23:12:01.343Z"
author: codex-audit-20260601
resolution: "Completed the June 1 pm CLI/SDK/ecosystem audit with sub-agent findings, targeted hardening, temp-project dogfood, telemetry/Sentry proof, PR #95, and review-agent feedback loop."
expected_result: "pm CLI and SDK audit findings are tracked, actionable issues are fixed, verification is green, review feedback is addressed, and the branch is ready to merge back to main."
actual_result: "Implemented agent-UX, deterministic equality, validate diagnostic, Sentry gate, extension docs, and bundle concurrency hardening; local verification and PR #95 checks passed; Gemini/Codex latest-head reviews reported no remaining issues."
comments[19]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-01T20:57:16.236Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Investigation note: Required orientation completed: pm context, pm search, pm list-open, pm list-in-progress. Existing broad audit lineage is closed; no in-progress duplicate found. Proceeding with bounded sub-agent review lanes and local dogfood/implementation."
  "2026-06-01T20:58:05.168Z",subagent-sdk-20260601,"Lane start: SDK/package ecosystem audit by subagent-sdk-20260601. Scope: package.json, sdk sources, package/extension runtime surfaces, docs/SDK.md, docs/EXTENSIONS.md, and init/install/contracts tests. Read-only lane; no file edits planned."
  "2026-06-01T20:58:07.865Z",subagent-docsci-20260601,"Lane start: docs/CI/observability audit reviewing progressive-disclosure docs, README/AGENTS links, GitHub workflows, changelog/release setup, secrets/privacy posture, Sentry/telemetry validation scripts, and free-service assumptions. No file edits planned."
  "2026-06-01T20:58:10.256Z",subagent-uxperf-20260601,"Lane start: CLI agent-UX/performance audit lane inspecting contracts/help/list/search/get/history/health/validate/reindex surfaces, compact defaults, parser recovery, startup/telemetry hot paths. Scope is read-only code audit; duplicate check reused pm-z0ip after context/search/list-open/list-in-progress."
  "2026-06-01T20:58:18.946Z",subagent-quality-20260601,"Quality lane start: inspecting complex/long files, duplicated logic/tests/docs, dead legacy code, dependency/type-safety risks, and low-risk optimization opportunities. No edits planned; duplicate check reused active lineage pm-z0ip."
  "2026-06-01T21:02:07.365Z",subagent-uxperf-20260601,"Lane final findings: 1) MED get --depth brief is not brief: src/cli/commands/get.ts:208-223 still emits empty body/linked shells and reads full history for claim_state; pm get pm-z0ip --json and --depth brief were both 1198 bytes vs --fields id,title,status,type,updated_at 213 bytes. Fix: omit body/linked on brief and gate claim_state history behind standard/deep or explicit field. 2) MED validate resolution JSON is token-heavy: src/cli/commands/validate.ts:776-795 emits up to 40 missing rows plus 40 full pm update commands by default; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json returned 37 rows and 37 remediation commands. Fix: default to counts/top-N and add explicit --verbose-diagnostics/--remediation-hints for full commands. 3) LOW reindex discoverability/package split: src/cli/commands/reindex.ts:474-770 exists, src/cli/commands/index.ts lacks runReindex export, pm reindex --help --json exits unknown_command while contracts package-owned hints point to search-advanced. Fix: either remove/move dead core implementation or register/package it consistently, and add search-advanced/reindex to rich package hints in src/cli/error-guidance.ts:75-80. No new pm items created."
  "2026-06-01T21:02:13.158Z",subagent-sdk-20260601,"Final SDK/package audit findings: found one concrete docs/example ergonomics defect fitting pm-z0ip. docs/EXTENSIONS.md minimal standalone extension imports @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk, but extension-only runtime cannot resolve that dependency unless the copied extension/package has its own package.json deps installed; isolated doctor repro returned extension_load_failed_sdk_dependency_missing. Suggested fix: split standalone extension snippets from package snippets or require package.json+npm install when using SDK imports, matching scaffold behavior. Evidence: pnpm build; targeted tests 9 files/217 tests passed; temp PM_PATH repro confirmed warning."
  "2026-06-01T21:02:52.317Z",subagent-quality-20260601,"Quality lane final: findings only, no edits. Medium: raw JSON.stringify equality in linked-test assertions/runtime filters/update-many is order-sensitive; use stableStringify/deep equality and add order-variant tests (src/cli/commands/test.ts:1293, src/core/schema/runtime-field-filters.ts:4-5, src/cli/commands/update-many.ts:355-356). Low: unused-symbol audit fails with stale helpers/imports, concentrated in extension loader/test command; run pnpm exec tsc --noEmit -p tsconfig.json --noUnusedLocals --noUnusedParameters and prune or convert public types to exports (src/core/extensions/loader.ts:8-10,19-21,48-49,82-110,946; src/cli/commands/test.ts:20,396-409; src/cli/commands/create.ts:316; src/core/search/cache.ts:365). Low optimization/risk: npm pack ships 262 dist source maps totaling 8.54MB of 14.02MB unpacked; decide whether npm package needs maps or exclude/upload separately (package.json:48-60). Verification: pnpm build, pnpm typecheck, pnpm quality:static, pnpm audit --audit-level moderate, pm health --check-only --summary --json, npm pack --dry-run --json."
  "2026-06-01T21:03:47.541Z",subagent-docsci-20260601,"Final docs/CI/observability audit findings: release.yml strict Sentry gate currently fails live with 0 critical/6 high unresolved; run-gates/coverage can fail under shared checkout because bundle-cli deletes dist/cli-bundle while tests use dist/cli.js; changelog:pm:check mutates .agents/pm/extensions/.managed-extensions.json timestamp via install side effect; release workflow uses bun-version latest. Verified docs links, docs-skills gate, security scan, changelog check, and telemetry freshness gate otherwise green; private telemetry docs remain ignored."
  "2026-06-01T21:08:35.432Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Evidence: Focused regression suite passed after final test placement: 6 files, 160 tests via node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/get-append-command.spec.ts tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts tests/unit/test-command.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts."
  "2026-06-01T21:19:09.855Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Evidence: Final focused regression suite passed: 7 files, 164 tests including CLI main Sentry suppression, release automation contracts, get/validate/test/update-many/help runtime coverage."
  "2026-06-01T21:52:31.425Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Review follow-up evidence: addressed Gemini/Codex findings by preserving stale bundle cleanup after successful esbuild metafile output, applying compact validate diagnostics to lifecycle/history/command-reference surfaces with verbose expansion, replacing stableStringify equality with primitive-safe stableValueEquals, and narrowing expected Sentry issue ignores to handled CLI errors only. Verified focused suite 8 files/171 tests, full coverage 135 files/2094 tests at 100%, package-first dogfood 87 commands, changelog check unchanged, typecheck/static/docs/security gates, Sentry strict and required telemetry gates."
  "2026-06-01T22:03:27.300Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Review follow-up: Gemini noted stale symlinks in dist/cli-bundle would not be collected by the post-build stale-file cleanup. Updated collectFiles to include Dirent symlinks and added release automation contract coverage. Verification: pnpm build and node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts."
  "2026-06-01T22:16:51.754Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Review follow-up: Codex found concurrent bundle cleanups could delete another build's fresh hashed chunks. Added a stale-aware .cli-bundle-build.lock around the esbuild output plus stale cleanup phase so builds serialize while the live bundle stays available for CLI users. Verification: pnpm build, pnpm typecheck, and node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts."
  "2026-06-01T22:22:28.609Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Review follow-up: Gemini found stale bundle-lock cleanup could delete a newly acquired lock if multiple builders detected the same stale lock. Changed stale cleanup to atomically rename the stale lock directory to a unique candidate before removing it, preserving mutual exclusion. Verification: pnpm build, pnpm typecheck, and node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts."
  "2026-06-01T22:32:02.982Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Review follow-up: Gemini/Codex found immediate stale bundle cleanup could affect already-running lazy imports, stale-lock retry could sleep after a released lock, RegExp values could compare equal through stableStringify, and the Sentry expected-error filter needed message-level narrowing. Added bundle stale-file retention, immediate retry on missing lock stats, RegExp-aware stableValueEquals, and a known expected handled CLI issue allowlist. Verification: pnpm build, pnpm typecheck, focused release/serialization tests, full coverage 135 files/2094 tests at 100%, Sentry strict gate, and required telemetry gate."
  "2026-06-01T22:39:20.297Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Review follow-up: Gemini found lock stat errors should only ignore ENOENT, stale symlink cleanup should inspect links with lstat, and Sentry issue payloads may omit isUnhandled. Updated bundle lock/file stat handling and relaxed the Sentry expected-message filter to reject only explicitly unhandled issues. CodeRabbit's pm history warning was reviewed as a false positive because all .agents/pm mutations in this branch were produced through pm CLI commands. Verification: pnpm build, pnpm typecheck, release automation contract test, Sentry strict gate with explicit personal token, and required telemetry gate."
  "2026-06-01T23:00:21.192Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Closure evidence: PR #95 latest head 47e4c3104d16175ab5979fca25177485af379f90 completed all GitHub checks green after the final review loop. Gemini review at 2026-06-01T22:41:48Z reported no feedback; Codex review comment at 2026-06-01T22:42:10Z reported no major issues; waited until 2026-06-01T23:00:11Z before close. Sourcery remained skipped due external rate limit, not a code failure."
  "2026-06-01T23:12:01.343Z",codex-audit-20260601,"Review follow-up after tracker close: Gemini found Date/Set/Map comparisons needed explicit stableValueEquals handling and stale bundle cleanup should not fail builds on non-critical file cleanup races. Added Date/Set/Map handling, robust cleanup swallowing for stale file lstat/unlink, and coverage assertions. Verification: serialization spec passed and full coverage 135 files/2094 tests at 100%."
